{"author":{"id":"798adc69106007f62b57768584b7e864cbdc2e90db33431f3b69bf5a958b3c99"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1606834014,"nonce":"r+BBanPT2qqWQaLYkoQux12O9Rk=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDczNjU5NzQ4OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/277#issuecomment-736597488"},"message":"I generate mine by logging into the swagger page at http://localhost:8000/swagger/, clicking `Django Login`, logging in with superuser credentials, then using the swagger page to call `GET /auth/token/`.\nRunning `./manage.py drf_create_token` generates the same token for me, so I think your problem is specifying the token in the request. The header should be formatted as `Authorization: Token e9d103cdb6bb1907a501282ac02b3d5265dac487`, not 'bearer'. This is a curl that works for me:\n```\ncurl -X POST \"http://localhost:8000/api/auth/token/\" -H  \"accept: application/json\" -H \"Authorization: Token e9d103cdb6bb1907a501282ac02b3d5265dac487\"\n```","files":null}]}